'''奧古斯特山'''（[[英语|英文]]：'''Mount Augustus'''）是位於[[澳大利亚|澳大利亚]][[西澳大利亚州|西澳大利亚州]]内陆沙漠地区的一座[[山|石山]]。该山被西方媒体广泛报道为世界最大的[[磐石|单体岩石]]（英文：Monolith）<ref>[http://www.mtaugustustouristpark.com/general-information.html General Information － Mt Augustus Tourist Park] {{Wayback|url=http://www.mtaugustustouristpark.com/general-information.html |date=20210118103812 }} {{en}}</ref><ref>{{Citation | author1=Tassell, Dave | title=Augustus: ancient giant of the west | journal=Australian Outdoors. Yearbook | publication-date=1978 | issue=1978 | pages=114–117 | url=http://trove.nla.gov.au/work/39258631 | accessdate=11 January 2014}} {{en}}</ref>。

== 世界最大的单体岩石 ==
奧古斯特山的海拔高度高於海平面{{convert|1106|m|ft}}，高於附近地面{{convert|860|m|ft}}。该山的底面積達4795公頃。据中文版乌鲁鲁官方网站<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://uluru-australia.com/zh-hans/about-uluru/uluru-facts/ |title=乌鲁鲁巨石的一些真相 |accessdate=2020-08-27 |archive-date=2020-09-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200905084658/https://uluru-australia.com/zh-hans/about-uluru/uluru-facts/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>以及多家英文媒体报道，该山为世界最大的单体岩石<ref>[https://www.smh.com.au/lifestyle/mount-augustus-20040208-gdkqzd.html Mount Augustus － The largest monolith in the world] {{Wayback|url=https://www.smh.com.au/lifestyle/mount-augustus-20040208-gdkqzd.html |date=20171010150624 }} {{en}}</ref><ref>[https://www.perthnow.com.au/opinion/peter-van-onselen/peter-van-onselen-why-dont-we-all-know-about-mt-augustus-ng-b88990257z Peter van Onselen: Why don't we all know about Mt Augustus?] {{Wayback|url=https://www.perthnow.com.au/opinion/peter-van-onselen/peter-van-onselen-why-dont-we-all-know-about-mt-augustus-ng-b88990257z |date=20200905084743 }} {{en}}</ref>，但也有学者对该说法提出了异议<ref>{{Citation | author1=Bourman, Robert P | author2=Ollier, Cliff | author3=Buckman, Solomon, Dr. | title=Mount Augustus geology and geomorphology | publication-date=2010-01-01 | publisher=Research Online | url=http://trove.nla.gov.au/work/73698414 | accessdate=11 January 2014 | archive-date=2020-01-29 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200129210220/https://trove.nla.gov.au/work/73698414 | dead-url=no }} - notably in the abstract: ''Mount Augustus has often been compared with Ayers Rock, and unwarranted claims have been made that it is the biggest rock in the world and the world's biggest monolith.'' and ''Other rock types present on Mount Augustus include metamorphic and igneous rocks, which preclude it from being termed a monolith.'' See abstract - [http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/j.1745-5871.2009.00608.x/abstract;jsessionid=16E8EC24BE6383BF75C5D6793A04711B.f02t02 Mount Augustus Geology and Geomorphology － Abstract] {{Wayback|url=http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/j.1745-5871.2009.00608.x/abstract;jsessionid=16E8EC24BE6383BF75C5D6793A04711B.f02t02 |date=20160304111430 }} {{en}}</ref>。

